The Asian Development Bank (ADB) said ithad approved two loans amounting to 75.7 mln dollars foragricultural projects in Bangladesh and Nepal.    It said both loans are repayable over 40 years, including a10-year grace, and carry a service charge of one pct a year.    The bank said it approved 51.7 mln for an agriculturalinputs program for Bangladesh aimed at sustaining foodgrainproduction.    It said the loan will cover the entire foreign exchangecomponent of the project's total cost of 65 mln.    The ADB said it approved 24 mln dlrs to support anagricultural credit project in Nepal.    The loan will benefit Nepal by increasing foodgrain output,augmenting production of milk and other dairy products andexpanding energy generation in rural areas, it said. REUTER&#3;